cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.LT, cs.FL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the design of languages for functional reactive programming, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). It specifically focuses on modal FRP languages and the use of Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) as a language for reactive programming, which are topics related to logic (cs.LO), temporal logic (cs.LT), and formal methods (cs.FL). The paper also discusses operational properties and programming with events and streams, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE).
